Inquiry Classes:

  OR89FRT => Inquiry regarding W-4 form and tax withholdings. Not for international employees.
   Inquiry Entity: 
     taxForm => W-4, W-2
     employeeNumber => \b\d{6}\b
OR37KRT => Questions about involuntary termination of a job or employee, workforce reduction, voluntary resignation, final salary payouts, or recovery of terminated employee's assets.
   Inquiry Entity:
     employeeNumber => \b\d{6}\b
OR27BRT => Inquiry regarding the Adoption Reimbursement program.
   Inquiry Entity:
     employeeRelative => son, daughter
     employeeNumber => \b\d{6}\b
OR37ART => Inquiry regarding the Tuition Reimbursement program. Not available for graduate programs.
   Inquiry Entity:
     employeeRelative => son, daughter
     employeeNumber => \b\d{6}\b
OR95JRT => Questions about the employee referral program, referral bonus and referring colleagues for job opportunities. Not applicable to consultants.
   Inquiry Entity:
     employeeNumber => \b\d{6}\b


Definitions:

Inquiry Classes:
  className: an identifier for inquiry class
  classDescription: the description for the inquiry class
Inquiry Entities:
  entityName: an identifier for the entity
  entityValue: an array of identifying values

Determine the correct inquiry class(es) for the statement below.  If there are corresponding entity values for the class(es), return those as well, embedded under the class.  All of the applicable information should be presented in YAML output.  Only inquiry class and inquiry entity information should be provided.  No other information is allowed. If other information is present, the YAML will be rejected and the user will not get the information they need.

Statement:
Employee 938571 resigned today based on the fact that their adopted daughter needs to attend a special school.  What is the process I need to start?
